cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

This paper is about weakly-supervised image segmentation, which is a task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep network that uses saliency information to improve the quality of object location cues, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses seeded region growing method, which is a common technique in image processing and computer vision, indicating that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories.
